Help Users Refine Search Results with Sorting for Cards

Provide an improved search experience to your users by adding options to sort search result cards. You can select up to 20 fields for sorting criteria, and users can sort by up to three fields when they view search results.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience editions where Criteria-Based Search and Filter is enabled.

Who: Users with the Criteria-Based Search and Filter system permission can configure and use criteria-based search and filter capabilities.

How: Add a search configuration that sorts search results shown as cards. From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Criteria, and then select Criteria-Based Search and Filter. On the Search Configuration tab, click New. Select Card as the display format of search results, and then select an OmniStudio FlexCard. For sorting criteria, move up to 20 fields from the Available Fields list to the Selected Fields list.
title: Improved Search Results Sorting for Cards
